# CREATING A CALCULATOR
# build a simple calculator that gets two inputs from the user and adds them together

# create two variables to add together


num1 = input("Enter a number: ")
num2 = input("Enter another number: ")

# the default input data type is a string, this has to be converted to a number
# int() only allows for whole numbers i.e., integers. float() allows for decimals also
result = float(num1) + float(num2)
print(result)
